SIMPLE: extol
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Extol
<hw>Ex*tol"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p.
p.</pos> <conjf>Extolled</conjf><pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Extolling</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[L. <ets>extollere</ets>;
<ets>ex</ets> out + <ets>tollere</ets> to lift, take up, or raise: cf.
OF. <ets>extoller</ets>. See <er>Tollerate</er>, and cf.
<er>Flate</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To place on high; to lift up; to
elevate.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Who <qex>extolled</qex> you in the half-crown boxes,⟦br⟧
Where you might sit and muster all the beauties.</q> <rj><qau>Beau. &
Fl.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To elevate by praise; to eulogize; to praise; to
magnify; <as>as, to <ex>extol</ex> virtue; to <ex>extol</ex> an act or a
person.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Wherein have I so deserved of you,⟦br⟧
That you <qex>extol</qex> me thus?</q> <rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj></p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- To praise; applaud; commend; magnify; celebrate;
laud; glorify. See <er>Praise</er>.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Extoller</ent>⟦br⟧
